Angola to Increase State Salaries by 30%; IMF Opposed to Plan, Jornal Says

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-05-30T11:12:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/angola-to-increase-state-salaries-by-30-imf-opposed-to-plan-jornal-says.html
Angola plans to increase salaries of
state workers by 30 percent, Novo Jornal reported, 
without saying where it got the information.  The  International Monetary Fund , which has a $1.4 billion
loan program with the southern African nation, is opposed to the
plan as it may boost inflation, the Luanda-based newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
 cmendes6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  